Aim: install ssh server

Step 1: Install OpenSSH Server Software Package
 command: sudo apt-get install openssh-server

Step 2: Enable ssh service
Command :- sudo sysytemctl start ssh

Step 3:-Step 3: Check sshd status
Check the status of the SSH daemon:
Command:- sudo systemctl status sshd


Step 4:-
First Update And Then Install OpenSSH server.
Command :- sudo apt update
Command :- sudo apt upgrade

Step 5:- Allow ssh through firewall and enable the firewall and check the status of firewall
command-sudo ufw allow ssh
command-sudo ufw enable
command-sudo ufw status

Step 6:- Testing
command-ssh kali@server-ip
or
command-ssh localhost
To configure the ssh, the file is located at /etc/ssh/sshd_config It contains options to configure the ssh.After configuring,
restart the service, and your changes will be applied.

Step6-to exit ssh 
command-exit 
